Big Bailey Johnson is Maya and Bailey’s father. Despite his lively personality, he is handsome, vain, and selfish. He stands out among the other rural blacks because of his proper English and his flashy possessions. Maya implies that Big Bailey’s pretensions result from his disenfranchisement as a black man in the United  States. Big Bailey does not respect, care for, or connect with Maya.Read anin-depth analysis of Big Bailey Johnson.